fibre /ˈfaɪbə/

(fibres) [美国英语] AM  fiber 

1. N-COUNT A fibre is a thin thread of a natural or artificial substance, especially one that is used to make cloth or rope. 纤维 

例： If you look at the paper under a microscope you will see the fibres. 如果你在显微镜下观察这张纸，你就会看到纤维。 

2. N-COUNT A fibre is a thin piece of flesh like a thread which connects nerve cells in your body or which muscles are made of. 纤维组织 

例： ...the nerve fibres. …神经纤维。 

3. N-VAR A particular fibre is a type of cloth or other material that is made from or consists of threads. 纤维制品 

例： The ball is made of rattan – a natural fibre. 这个球是用藤–一种天然纤维制成的。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Fibre consists of the parts of plants or seeds that your body cannot digest. Fibre is useful because it makes food pass quickly through your body. (植物) 纤维 

例： Most vegetables contain fibre. 大多数蔬菜含有纤维。

</div>

